\begin_layout Paragraph
Profit Maximization.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Firm optimization unfolds over two stages.
 First, firms determine their production structure 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{j},\omega_{f}$
\end_inset

.
 Second, R&D is allocated, input and final prices are determined, and goods
 are produced and consumed.
 I start by characterizing the second stage.
 In particular, the downstream firms choose final prices and R&D:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\pi_{j}\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)=\max_{p_{j},\{I_{j,A,c},I_{j,I,c}\}_{c}}D\left(p_{j}\right)^{-\sigma}\left(p_{j}-c_{j}\left(\{p_{f,j}\}_{f},\{I_{j,A,c},I_{j,I,c}\},\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j},\boldsymbol{\mathcal{I}},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)\right)-\sum_{c\in C_{j}}r_{c}\Bigl(I_{j,A,c}+I_{j,I,c}\Bigr)\label{eq:Upstream-Profits-Param}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $D=\bar{D}P^{\sigma-1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P^{1-\sigma}=\sum_{j}p_{j}^{1-\sigma}$
\end_inset

.
 Then, upstream firms determine R&D.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\pi_{j}\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)=\max_{\{I_{f,c},\{I_{f,j,c}\}_{f}\}_{c}}\sum_{j}q_{f,j}\left(p_{f,j}-c_{f,j}\left(\{I_{f,c},I_{f,j,c}\},\boldsymbol{\omega}_{f},\boldsymbol{\mathcal{I}},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)\right)-\sum_{c\in C_{f}}r_{c}\Bigl(I_{f}+\sum_{j}I_{f,j}\Bigr)\label{eq:Downstream-Profits-Param}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

And finally, input prices are determined simultaneously by OEM's take it
 or leave it offer.
 OEM's, utilizing their larger market position, choose input prices that
 minimize their input expenditure subject to the participation of their
 supplier: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
p_{f,j}=\arg\min_{p_{f,j}}\underbrace{D\left(p_{j}\right)^{-\sigma}\frac{p_{j,I}}{I_{j,I}^{\alpha}}\frac{p_{f,j}^{-\theta}}{p_{j,I}^{1-\theta}}}_{\equiv q_{f,j}}p_{f,j}\text{ \text{subject to }}\tilde{\pi}_{f,j}>0.\label{eq:OEM-offer}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The condition 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{\pi}_{f,j}>0$
\end_inset

 is a participation constraint that ensures that supplier 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 makes positive profits from supplier 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 accounting for 
\begin_inset Formula $j's$
\end_inset

 contribute to the R&D expenses.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The explicit participation constrain is listed in Appendix Section X.
 It requires that OEMs compensate suppliers for the entire specialized R&D
 expenses and their relative share of the generic R&D expenditure.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The stage-1 problem is then to choose the production structure that maximizes
 the stage 2 profits: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j}}\pi_{j}\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)-f\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j}\right)\text{ and \ensuremath{\max_{\boldsymbol{\omega}_{f}}}\pi_{f}\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{f},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\right)}-f\left(\boldsymbol{\omega}_{j}\right).
\]

\end_inset

I do not characterize the optimal choices at this point.
 The estimation will condition on the observes production structure, and
 counterfactuals will consider exogenous changes in production structure.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In the future, I plan to solve this problem and compute counterfactuals.
 I additionally want to consider strategic behavior by firms at the point
 where production structure are determined.
 That is, compute firms' best-responses to their competitors strategies,
 anticipating the effect of all production structure on the aggregate state:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{\omega_{j}}\pi_{j}\left(\omega_{j},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\left(\left\{ \omega_{-j},\omega_{f}\right\} \right)\right)-f\left(\omega_{j}\right)\text{ and \ensuremath{\max_{\omega_{f}}}\pi_{f}\left(\omega_{f},\boldsymbol{\Omega}\left(\left\{  \omega_{j},\omega_{-f}\right\}  \right) \right)}-f\left(\omega_{j}\right).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

