 Their new optimization problem is then: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{I_{f}}\tilde{x}_{j}\frac{\mu-1}{\mu}\frac{\left(\mu\bar{c}_{f,j}I_{f}^{-2\rho}\right)^{1-\theta}}{\left(\mu\bar{c}_{f,j}I_{f}^{-2\rho}\right)^{-\theta}+\left(p_{\text{\text{Foreign}}}\right)^{-\theta}}-2rI_{f}
\]

\end_inset

The firm's optimal R&D spending then satisfies
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
I_{f}^{\rho}=\left(\left(\rho\left(\theta-1\right)\lambda_{f}-\rho\left(\theta\right)\lambda_{f}^{2}\right)\frac{\tilde{x}_{j}}{r}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{f}=(\mu\bar{c}_{f,j}I_{f}^{-\rho})^{-\theta}/((\mu\bar{c}_{f,j}I_{f}^{-\rho})^{-\theta}+(p_{\text{\text{Foreign}}})^{-\theta}).$
\end_inset

 In the limiting case where 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{\text{Foreign}}\rightarrow\infty$
\end_inset

, then there is no incentive to invest as suppliers already capture the
 whole market and cost reduction will only lower the price they charge.
 A shock from foreign competition can lead to more innovation as firms now
